guide/src/format/mdbook.md
     3‚Üí## Hiding code lines
     5‚ÜíThere is a feature in mdBook that lets you hide code lines by prepending them with a specific prefix.
     6‚Üí
     7‚ÜíFor the Rust language, you can prefix lines with `# ` (`#` followed by a space) to hide them [like you would with Rustdoc][rustdoc-hide].
     8‚ÜíThis prefix can be escaped with `##` to prevent the hiding of a line that should begin with the literal string `# ` (see [Rustdoc's docs][rustdoc-hide] for more details)
     9‚Üí
    10‚Üí[rustdoc-hide]: https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/rustdoc/write-documentation/documentation-tests.html#hiding-portions-of-the-example
    11‚Üí
    12‚Üí```bash
    13‚Üí# fn main() {
    14‚Üí    let x = 5;
    15‚Üí    let y = 6;
    16‚Üí
    17‚Üí    println!("{}", x + y);
    18‚Üí# }
    19‚Üí```
    20‚Üí
    21‚ÜíWill render as
    22‚Üí
    23‚Üí```rust
